abstract: Donald Trump, Coronavirus, Avalanche: Here’s what you need to know.
snippet: Donald Trump, Coronavirus, Avalanche: Here’s what you need to know.
lead_paragraph: The U.S. Senate has acquitted President Trump on charges that he abused his power and obstructed Congress to aid his own re-election.

abstract: Joe Biden entered the Democratic presidential race as a favorite, the candidate with the longest resume, a network of establishment donors and a pitch that he could win the kind of voters who would defeat President Donald Trump.
snippet: Joe Biden entered the Democratic presidential race as a favorite, the candidate with the longest resume, a network of establishment donors and a pitch that he could win the kind of voters who would defeat President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: SOMERSWORTH, N.H. — Joe Biden entered the Democratic presidential race as a favorite, the candidate with the longest resume, a network of establishment donors and a pitch that he could win the kind of voters who would defeat President Donald Trump.

abstract: On a private conference call, Iowa Democratic leaders revealed more about how the reporting process on Monday night went calamitously awry.
snippet: On a private conference call, Iowa Democratic leaders revealed more about how the reporting process on Monday night went calamitously awry.
lead_paragraph: Iowa Democratic officials said on a private conference call on Wednesday night that nearly all the much-delayed results of Monday’s caucuses would be released by Thursday, although a few precincts might remain outstanding.

abstract: Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts, fresh from an Iowa finish that was a step behind the race’s two leaders, changed little of her go-to rhetoric during a CNN town hall event Wednesday in New Hampshire, where she stressed that she remained the best candidate to rid Washington of corruption.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts, fresh from an Iowa finish that was a step behind the race’s two leaders, changed little of her go-to rhetoric during a CNN town hall event Wednesday in New Hampshire, where she stressed that she remained the best candidate to rid Washington of corruption.

headline_main: Elizabeth Warren says that ‘in 2020 we should have a woman president.’

abstract: The Iowa Democratic Party released another batch of results Wednesday night, and once again the leaders were unchanged: Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead of state delegate equivalents over Bernie Sanders, with Elizabeth Warren in third and Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Amy Klobuchar further behind.
lead_paragraph: The Iowa Democratic Party released another batch of results Wednesday night, and once again the leaders were unchanged: Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead of state delegate equivalents over Bernie Sanders, with Elizabeth Warren in third and Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Amy Klobuchar further behind.

abstract: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. said on Wednesday that his performance in the Iowa caucuses had fallen short of his expectations, though he played down the significance of the contest in the overall nominating process.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. said on Wednesday that his performance in the Iowa caucuses had fallen short of his expectations, though he played down the significance of the contest in the overall nominating process.
headline_main: Biden at CNN town hall says ‘I expected to do better’ in Iowa.

abstract: Mr. Biden has gone on the offensive, taking aim at two rivals ahead of him in the Iowa results, Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders, while Ms. Warren continues to stress unity.
snippet: Mr. Biden has gone on the offensive, taking aim at two rivals ahead of him in the Iowa results, Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders, while Ms. Warren continues to stress unity.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Senator Elizabeth Warren each suffered a damaging setback in Iowa that could make it harder for them to recover next week in New Hampshire — and not just because they were running well behind the leading candidates as Democrats awaited a final count.

abstract: The growing extremism of the debate alienates many people on the left and right.
snippet: The growing extremism of the debate alienates many people on the left and right.
lead_paragraph: Where will abortion opponents stand in 2020? President Trump recently made his bid for their votes, becoming the first president to speak in person at the annual March for Life in Washington, an event held since 1974. Two days later, a Democratic presidential hopeful, Pete Buttigieg, told a woman who called herself a “proud pro-life Democrat” that he would not support more moderate abortion language in the Democratic National Committee platform — basically suggesting that, on this issue, she will not find affirmation or support from her party.
